The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Pelosi in Syria 

 Damascus, April 3 (Reuters): US House speaker Nancy Pelosi arrived in Syria on Tuesday for a meeting with President Bashar al-Assad which the White House had described as a bad idea. 

Pelosi said she had no illusions but great hope for the talks. 

 US storms 

 Miami (Reuters): The 2007 Atlantic hurricane season will be far more active than usual with 17 tropical storms, of which nine will grow into hurricanes, a US forecasting team said on Tuesday. 

 Japan plane 

 Tokyo (Reuters): A plane carrying 259 people, including Japanese finance minister Koji Omi, made a safe emergency landing at an airport in southern Japan. 

 Billings dead 

 Melbourne (AP): John Billings, the founder of a Roman Catholic-friendly natural contraception method, died at a Melbourne retirement home. He was 89. 

 China gay site 

 Beijing (Reuters): Internet users in China will be able to watch the countrys first specialised gay chat show online on Thursday, the shows producer said. 




